  "doc_id": "14104",
  "text": "The present study also demonstrated for the first time that the combination of empagliflozin and linagliptin reduced the collagen deposition (Sirius red staining areas) and the expression of α-SMA protein, a marker of activated myofibroblasts (hepatic stellate cells) [CITATION_1] , around the central veins, as well as decreasing the expression of type 1 and 3 collagen mRNA. It has been suggested that α-SMA may be a valuable marker for evaluation of stellate cell activation and progression of hepatic fibrosis [CITATION_2] . If this combination therapy can prevent hepatic fibrosis, an advanced stage of NASH, it could subsequently stop progression to cirrhosis and HCC in NASH patients with diabetes.",
